{
  "texts": [
    "Ghazali et al. (2009) argued that instructors not only taught students but also affected how they think regarding education, school, and the subjects they taught.",
    "Teachers could have both positive and negative impacts on language learners.",
    "A teacher equipped with a pleasant personality, effective communication skills, professional knowledge, sincerity and commitment, and better skills management would help second language learners develop positive attitudes and acquire proficiency in the language (Getie, 2020).",
    "As a teacher was often imitated by his students, he was very closely observed by his second language learning learners.",
    "Larsen and Long (1991) asserted that the teacher was one of the crucial elements that had a considerable influence on the attitudes of second/foreign language learners and their entire learning process."
  ]
}